cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on deep learning and adversarial attacks, which are commonly studied in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the need for robustness against attacks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a new mechanism for adversarial defense, which involves training a model with limited data, which is a problem commonly studied in the field of neural networks (cs.NE).
